description: For sale in our Atlanta Showroom is a targa top 1986 Chevrolet Corvette. With an owner stated 51,867 miles actual, it's a well preserved example of fine 80s muscle. Powering this little C4 Corvette is a 5.7 liter TPI fuel injected Chevrolet small block V8 engine. With short runners for nice low end torque, these C4 Corvettes are known for being street light cruisers. With TPI tuned-port injection fuel injection, you get the fun of a V8 without the fuel consumption of a pesky carburetor. With an owner stated numbers matching drivetrain, this Corvette has withstood the testament of time. Backing the small block V8 is a 700r4 4-speed automatic transmission with overdrive. With fuel injection and a nice overdrive gear, these Vettes are known for pulling out great fuel economy when highway driving. The power is thrown to the pavement via a Dana independent rear suspension and factory aluminum/alloy wheels wrapped in radial tires. With a fully independent suspension, this C4 Corvette for sale is great at flattening hills and straightening curves. If the performance doesn't grab you, the sharp lines will. The exterior is a bright and shiny shade of Gold. The sleek and narrow lines with gills, mixed with the Metallic Gold finish, make the Corvette look like a shark floating down the highway. A great tribute to its ancestors, this Corvette has that sporty look that can only be had by owning a Corvette. The interior is clean, with Tan leather buckets. With the automatic shifter tucked between the buckets, you have a fighter pilot cockpit feel, which adds to the enjoyment of driving this Corvette. The glass targa top is great for both sunny and overcast days. Pop off the top and you get the joy of a convertible, without all of the road noise. Options on this 1986 Chevrolet corvette for sale, include: A/C, AM/FM radio, cassette, glass targa top, lumbar support, power anti-lock brakes, power steering, power locks, power seats, power windows, tilt wheel, seat belts, leather interior, and aluminum alloy wheels wrapped in radial tires. To view the car in greater detail, including 100+ HD photos and HD video, please visit www.gatewayclassiccars.com. For more information please call the Atlanta showroom at 678-894-4833 or e-mail us at Atlanta@GatewayClassicCars.com.
